    "body": "this is fine -- v1 and v2 do not form surround votes\r\n\r\nand the definition supports liveness of the protocol -- e.g. a validator votes for some target and later changes to a different target as the rest of the validator set moved to this later target for whatever reason\r\n\r\nthe way the slashing conditions work, after a vote by a validator has been finalized, it cannot change unless that validator did something provably slashble",
